To remove the HTML tags and display the message as plain text, 
you need to parse the HTML string and extract the content without the tags.
In Flutter, you can use the flutter_html package to render HTML content 
directly in a widget, or if you prefer to strip out the HTML tags entirely, 
you can use the html package.


Option 1: Render HTML Content with flutter_html
If you want to render the content with the formatting specified by the HTML tags (like bold text), you can use the flutter_html package:

Add flutter_html to your pubspec.yaml:

yaml
Copy code
dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  flutter_html: ^2.2.1
Import the package and use it in your widget:

dart
Copy code
import 'package:flutter_html/flutter_html.dart';

// Inside your widget
Html(
  data: messageData.message,
);
Option 2: Strip HTML Tags and Display Plain Text
If you prefer to display the content without any HTML formatting, you can strip out the tags:

Add the html package to your pubspec.yaml:

yaml
Copy code
dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  html: ^0.15.0
Import the package and use it to strip HTML tags:

dart
Copy code
import 'package:html/parser.dart' as htmlParser;
import 'package:html/dom.dart' as htmlDom;

// Function to remove HTML tags
String parseHtmlString(String htmlString) {
  final document = htmlParser.parse(htmlString);
  final String parsedString = htmlParser.parse(document.body?.text).documentElement?.text ?? "";
  return parsedString;
}

// Inside your widget
Text(
  parseHtmlString(messageData.message ?? "No data available"),
);
Explanation:
flutter_html: This package renders the HTML content in a RichText widget, respecting the HTML tags.
html package: The parseHtmlString function uses the html package to parse the HTML string, extract the text, and return a plain string without any HTML tags.
By using one of these methods, you can either display the message with its HTML formatting or strip the HTML tags and show the content as plain text.
